        {
          "id": "a9c13431fa38_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ebf5",
          "text": "Which future will we guide ourselves toward as a species?",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*Cp_4fsL7eXDHxL-Vc20i3Q.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "a9c13431fa38_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f396",
          "text": "The future for humanity is a stark choice between extinction and planetary thriving. Will we become “wise managers” of cultural evolution before it’s too late? This may be THE most important question you will answer in word and deed in your lifetime.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "a9c13431fa38_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "689a",
          "text": "Almost no one realizes that we collectively know everything we need to solve our planetary crisis. Yet the gap between knowledge gathered and wisdom practiced remains very far indeed. Our current trajectory is “overshoot-and-collapse” as we move toward a future no one wants because we are blind to our great capacities for collective re-imagining in times of crisis.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 67,
              "href": "http://www.kosmosjournal.org/article/the-predicament-of-knowledge-a-challenge-for-culture-design/",
